<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Would-Be NYC Burglar Hangs Himself </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A man who broke into a clothing store through  
the roof caught his sweater on a piece of metal and accidentally 
hanged himself, police said Sunday. His body was found by the 
store's owner. 
</P>
<P>
	Terrence Adams, 55, apparently tried to enter the store to  
burglarize it when he became entangled, ``causing him to hang 
himself,'' said Officer Lee Tracy-Ader, a police spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
	Police had no other details, but news reports said the owner of  
the Dum Dum Boutique discovered the body when he arrived Saturday 
morning to open the store. 
</P>
<P>
	Adams apparently had lowered himself to a rear window but became  
trapped as he tried to slip between metal bars, it said. 
</P>
<P>
	The New York Post said Adams had a record of arrests for  
burglary. It quoted his wife, Ann Marie, as saying he was a Vietnam 
veteran who still carried a bullet in his back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
