<HEADLINE> Volkswagen Reports Record Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WOLFSBURG, Germany (AP) -- Automaker Volkswagen AG posted a 9.6  
percent rise Saturday in worldwide group unit sales in the first 
quarter, compared with the first quarter of 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	The group, which includes the Volkswagen brand as well as Audi,  
Skoda and SEAT, sold a record 1.78 million vehicles worldwide, 
Volkswagen said. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said unit sales in its Volkswagen brand rose 16.9  
percent to 750,504 vehicles in the first three months of the year. 
</P>
<P>
	In Western Europe, Volkswagen brand sales rose 30.9 percent to  
458,866 units. And in March in Germany alone, Volkswagen sold 
73,395 units, a year-on-year rise of 10.6 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
