under 20 years old. Nigerian coach Tunde Disu was fired within an 
hour after the game and had a police escort when leaving the 
stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	This was Nigeria's second defeat, and many thought it would lead  
to its elimination in the tournament, the first this country has 
held at the international level. 
</P>
<P>
	However, Nigeria remained in contention following results from  
later games Saturday. The Nigerians advance to the second round and 
on Wednesday play Ireland in the northern city of Kano. 
