	Guillen, 23, tore the anterior cruciate ligament hurt Saturday  
night after tagging out Tony Phillips in a rundown. Guillen started 
all five Mariners games this season. He played the first three at 
second base and moved over to shortstop after All-Star Alex 
Rodriguez was injured. 
