<HEADLINE> U.S. Duo Win Volleyball Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ACAPULCO, Mexico (AP) -- Americans Ian Clark and Bill Bouilliane  
upset top-ranked Brazilians Para Ferreira and Guilhermo Marques 
15-10 to win the FIVB Olympic-qualifying World Beach Volleyball 
Tour event today. 
</P>
<P>
	The No. 1-ranked Brazilian duo Adriana Behar and Shelda Bede  
claimed the women's title with a 15-11 victory over Kerri Pottharst 
and Pauline Manser of Australia. 
</P>
<P>
	Clark and Bouilliane, seeded 14th, used hard serves and during  
the 51-minute match to beat Ferreira-Marques, the reigning FIVB 
world champions after claiming the title in 1997 in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first time a U.S. men's team has won an FIVB event  
since an October 1996 tournament in Brazil. 
</P>
<P>
	``We never felt that we were underdogs going into it. We played  
well all weekend and we were confident,'' Bouilliane said. 
</P>
<P>
	In the women's competition, Behar-Bede earned their fifth  
straight event title. The team was making its 26th final-four 
appearance in 28 FIVB tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
	The International Federation of Beach Volleyball tournament in  
Acapulco was the second of 12 Olympic-qualifying events for the men 
and the first of nine for the women. 
</P>
</TEXT>
