</P>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Chicago Bulls managed save some face tonight,  
as they increased their offensive output to 81 points. But it still 
wasn't enough as they followed their 49-point debacle with an 87-81 
loss to the Boston Celtics tonight. Antoine Walker scored 16 of his 
23 points in the second half as the Celtics posted just their 
second home win in their last nine games. Chicago, which lost 82-49 
at home Saturday against Miami to shatter the NBA record for fewest 
points, has lost four straight and five in a row on the road. 

</P>
<P>
	Spain's Olazabal Wins Masters  
</P>
<P>
	AUGUSTA, Ga. (AP) -- Jose Maria Olazabal marched to victory at  
Augusta National today with a back-nine performance that left Greg 
Norman with another Masters disappointment. The 33-year-old 
Spaniard, who once used to cry himself to sleep and wonder if he 
would ever walk again, admitted that wearing the tournament's 
trademark green jacket a second time was an achievement that never 
crossed his mind. Olazabal shot a final round 1-Under-Par 71 for a 
two-stroke win over Davis Love to win his second career Masters. 


</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by LISI de BOURBON  
</P>
