<HEADLINE> Good and Tough Wins Commonweath Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Good and Tough found an opening at the top  
of the stretch to win the $201,300 Grade II Commonwealth Breeders' 
Cup on Sunday at Keeneland. 
</P>
<P>
	Good and Tough, ridden by Shane Sellers, took the lead from  
Crucible with an eighth of a mile to go and pulled away for a 
1 1/2-length victory. It was his second consecutive victory and 
seventh in 15 career starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Good and Tough, the 4-year-old son of Carson City, paid $4.40  
and 2.80. Purple Passion finished second and returned $4. 
</P>
