<HEADLINE> Good Samaritan Attacked in Mass. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANDOVER, Mass. (AP) -- A man who tried to help a motorist whose  
truck had rolled was punched in the jaw by the accident victim, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I thought maybe he was in shock,'' said John DeFronzo, 33. ``I  
didn't know how to take it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	DeFronzo said he saw the accident on Interstate 495 on Friday  
and stopped to help the driver, who apparently had lost control of 
his Chevy pickup truck and rolled over. 
</P>
<P>
	DeFronzo said when he initially approached 19-year-old Robert  
Lebel, the accident victim punched him in the jaw. 
</P>
<P>
	Lebel then allegedly warned DeFronzo and other motorists to stay  
back and then came after DeFronzo with a tire iron. 
</P>
<P>
	He then stole the pickup truck of another man who had stopped to  
help, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police arrested Lebel after finding him watching television in  
the living room of a house he allegedly had broken into. 
</P>
<P>
	Lebel faces charges that include assault and battery with a  
dangerous weapon and carjacking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
