<HEADLINE> Blue Jays put Bush on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Toronto Blue Jays put Homer Bush on the  
15-day disabled list today with a finger injury that could keep him 
sidelined up to a month. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush, obtained from the New York Yankees in the Roger Clemens  
deal, sustained a tear in his right index finger while sliding into 
second base in a game against the Baltimore Orioles on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	His finger will be immobilized for two weeks and he could miss  
three or four weeks, team officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bush was 5-for-16 with two RBIs in four games after hitting .284  
with one homer and 13 RBIs this spring. 
</P>
<P>
	He was replaced on the roster by infielder Norberto Martin, who  
started at second base Sunday against the Orioles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
