<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits Second Home Run </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire homered for the first time since  
opening day, connecting for his second off Jason Bere of the 
Cincinnati Reds on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	With two outs and none on in the first inning, McGwire lined a  
first-pitch fastball from Bere over the left-field wall, a drive 
estimated at 394 feet. 
</P>
<P>
	He'd been 3-for-14 with four walks, two strikeouts and one RBI  
since hitting his first homer off Milwaukee's David Weathers in the 
fifth inning on Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, McGwire homered in each of the first four games to  
tie the major league record set by Willie Mays in 1971. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire hit only one home run against the Reds last year, No. 60  
off Dennis Reyes on Sept. 5. For his career, he has three homers 
and five RBIs against the Reds, going 10-for-49 (.204). 
</P>
<P>
	Unlike Weathers, Bere was among McGwire's 70 victims last year.  
McGwire hit No. 29 on June 8 at Comiskey Park when Bere was 
pitching for the Chicago White Sox. Bere was released by Chicago 
and claimed on waivers by Cincinnati last July 21. 
</P>
<P>
	Raul Mondesi of the Los Angeles Dodgers began the day with the  
major league lead in home runs with four. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
