<HEADLINE> Worthy Crane Left Behind in Gate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stewards declared Worthy Crane a non-starter in  
today's fourth race at Aqueduct after he was inadvertently left 
behind at the starting gate when the race began. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was basically all my mistake,'' NYRA starter Bobby Duncan  
said. ``Another horse had broken open his stall door and I had gone 
over to instruct the gate crew member on him I wanted him to handle 
the horse. Basically, I lost track of the outside horse (Worthy 
Crane).'' 
</P>
<P>
	NYRA president and chief operating officer Terry Meyocks said,  
``We would like to apologize to the owner, trainer and connections 
of Worthy Crane as well as to the fans here and nationally who 
wagered on the horse. It was an unfortunate mistake.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Refunds were issued on wagers on Worthy Crane.  
</P>
