<HEADLINE> Sci-Fi Film 'Matrix' Takes in $22M / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The special effects-filled adventure ``The  
Matrix'' held its No. 1 spot at the box office, while spring break 
crowds gave Drew Barrymore's back-to-school film ``Never Been 
Kissed'' a strong opening, estimates showed. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Matrix,'' bringing in $22.2 million, stars Keanu Reeves in  
the story of a computer hacker who finds out that reality isn't 
what it seems. The film has emerged as the year's second breakout 
hit, grossing $72.9 million in just two weeks, according to 
estimates released Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Analyze This'' was the year's first breakout hit.  
</P>
<P>
	But not even the wizardry of ``The Matrix'' could pull the year  
out of its post-''Titanic'' syndrome. After a momentary upturn when 
``The Matrix'' opened, the overall box office was once again down 
last weekend, this time 4.4 percent, from last year's weekend, when 
``City of Angels,'' ``Lost in Space'' and ``Titanic'' were going 
strong. 
</P>
<P>
	With more than half the nation's young people on vacation last  
week, youth-oriented films predictably dominated the top 10 -- with 
a mixed bag of results. 
</P>
<P>
	``Never Been Kissed,'' with a strong $11.7 million, led the  
pack. The hip-hop comedy ``Foolish'' opened with $2.26 million in 
10th place for an impressive per-screen average of $7,410 -- even 
though its studio, fearing bad reviews, didn't screen the movie for 
critics. 
</P>
<P>
	``10 Things I Hate About You,'' the loose adaptation of  
Shakespeare's ``The Taming of the Shrew,'' slid 38 percent in its 
second week to finish fourth with $5.2 million. The movie played 
particularly well to vacationing teen-age girls. 
</P>
<P>
	But another new film, the Sundance Film Festival favorite ``Go''  
opened with a somewhat disappointing $4.7 million for sixth. Sony 
is now counting on strong word of mouth to keep the critically 
praised rave-scene film from plummeting into oblivion when most 
kids go back to school this week. 
</P>
<P>
	Estimated grosses for Friday through Sunday at North American  
theaters, according to Exhibitor Relations Co. Inc. Final figures 
to be released Monday: 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``The Matrix,'' $22.2 million.  
</P>
<P>
	2. ``Never Been Kissed,'' $11.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	3. ``The Out-Of-Towners,'' $5.3 million.  
</P>
<P>
	4. ``10 Things I Hate About You,'' $5.2 million.  
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Analyze This,'' $5.1 million.  
</P>
<P>
	6. ``Go,'' $4.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Forces of Nature,'' $3.7 million.  
</P>
<P>
	8. ``Twin Dragons,'' $2.8 million.  
</P>
<P>
	9. ``Doug's 1st Movie,'' $2.3 million.  
</P>
<P>
	10. ``Foolish,'' $2.26 million.  
</P>
</TEXT>
