<HEADLINE> Fires Close South Florida Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- A smoldering 600-acre fire flared back into life  
early Sunday, closing part of a rural road for a second time. 
</P>
<P>
	The Florida Highway patrol closed 15 miles of road for about six  
hours Sunday, said Renee Chidnese with the Florida Division of 
Forestry. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators do not know what restarted the fire. However, the  
area in a mostly undeveloped area of southern Miami-Dade County is 
thick with maleleuca trees, which ignite easily and produce a lot 
of smoke, Ms. Chidnese said. 
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere, a 450-acre fire in North Carolina that forced  
evacuation of more than 50 homes was declared contained early 
Sunday. No one was injured, no houses were damaged and the evacuees 
were allowed to return home late Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
