<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Telecom May Sell to Murdoch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILAN, Italy (AP) -- Telecom Italia is again considering the sale  
of a stake in its pay TV unit Stream to Rupert Murdoch's News 
Corp., the financial newspaper Il Sole 24 Ore reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia declined to comment and officials at News Corp.  
couldn't be reached. 
</P>
<P>
	Il Sole said the deal could involve the communication company  
Cecchi Gori, a new venture that includes first-division soccer 
teams Lazio, Roma, Parma and Cecchi Gori's Fiorentina. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecom Italia signed a preliminary deal late last year to sell  
Stream to Murdoch but it fell apart when Italy limited ownership of 
certain soccer rights. 
</P>
<P>
	Il Sole said News Corp. is one of several potential partners in  
a new deal, along with France's Canal Plus, Microsoft Corp.'s Web 
TV and other U.S. TV companies. 
</P>
<P>
	The sale of Stream and other non-core assets is part of Telecom  
Italia's attempt to fend off a hostile takeover bid from Olivetti. 

</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
