<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> MetroStars 2, Mutiny 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- New York-New Jersey goalkeeper Mike Ammann  
stopped three of four shootout shots as the MetroStars beat the 
Tampa Bay Mutiny 2-1 on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mark Chung, Mike Sorber and Roy Myers scored as the MetroStars  
won the shootout 3-1. Jan Eriksson had the lone Mutiny shootout 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
	``My part is to just be aggressive and try and get out as quick  
as I can,'' said Ammann, who is 9-2 all-time in shootouts. ``You 
still have to react and just be lucky at times.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ammann was spectacular throughout the match, making eight saves.  
He stopped Alejandro Sequiera's point-blank header in the 86th 
minute. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars are off to their best-ever start at 3-1.  
</P>
<P>
	``Our record is good, but more importantly we have more  
confidence each game,'' MetroStars coach Bora Milutinovic said. 
</P>
<P>
	Eduardo Hurtado put the MetroStars up 1-0 on a penalty kick  
during the 28th minute. It was the forward's third goal of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Since acquiring Hurtado from the Los Angeles Galaxy last season,  
the MetroStars are 15-2 when the forward records a point. 
</P>
<P>
	Musa Shannon tied it at 1 in the 62nd minute. The Tampa Bay  
forward scored for the second consecutive match after entering as a 
second half substitution. 
</P>
<P>
	Tampa Bay fell to 0-3 and has now started the past two seasons  
by dropping its first three games. 
</P>
<P>
	MetroStars midfielder Tab Ramos, who continues to experience  
right leg pain, did not make the trip. It is not known when Ramos, 
who missed his third straight game, will return. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
